main event: An unidentified flying object was reported in Newburgh, New York on April 16, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as having red, yellow, and green lights at about 20-30 degrees elevation., The object moved slowly and resembled a weather balloon., It was observed for a duration of about 5 minutes., The observer could not identify the object as any aircraft in the area., No physical evidence was documented.
sighted object: an unidentified flying object with colored lights
witness description: A civilian observer who reported the sighting.
